<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-01T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-01T17:00:00-05:00" n="912" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d912">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 124.55/8</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Belgium</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WB1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Whitlock</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-01T17:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 1, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>261. Department’s 256, February 26, 5 p.m., and your 44, February 26, 7
                            p.m. Department wishes to avoid giving appearance that either Legation
                            or commission is withdrawing voluntarily from Belgium. Inasmuch as all
                            former privileges to members of relief commission have apparently been
                            restored, you should not leave until instructed further. <persName corresp="#p_HH1">Hoover</persName> wishes members of commission to
                            remain for the present but to depart with you in case of your
                            withdrawal.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>